page.title: 17MORRIS MEN,FENSTANTON
page.content: There are two sides of{Morris {Dancers in Fenstanton. {Fenstanton Morris Men}started dancing before 1981. {Cromwell Morris Men}started dancing in 1981 and some of the Fenstanton men joined Cromwell. {Fenstanton}dance at dawn on{May Day {by The Clock Tower.}They dance mostly on special occasions like{Boxing_Day. {Cromwell}had their first meet in Great Paxton in November 1981.They met in a pub called'The Bell',in early 1982. They moved to Abbotsley Hall in 1983.They often practice in this Hall from September_April. They danced once in Fenstanton, because there was bad feelings from the Fenstanton Morris men.They have danced in Swavesey,Needingworth and Biggleswade. {There are thirteen or {fourteen members in each group.
